nts1.n: THE ONE GLOVE BREAKFAST SHOW W/ MACCA
nts1.d: Stay left and take a trip with Macca's Saturday breakfast show on NTS. Weekend musings and eclectic cuts from all over the place, it's a low-key affair and you're all invited. ONE GLOVE!!!

Ross Allen knows music. Mainly new but plenty of old. The broadest range of music that moves dance floors from across the era’s and across the planet. On his regular Foundation Music Specials he invites guests to share their histories and seminal tracks…
Manchester's Tarzsa brings good vibes Soul, RnB & Jazz to the NTS airwaves once a month.

nts1.n: THE EXTENDED PLAY SESSIONS W/ MR PEDRO & For Mankind
nts1.d: Long time record collector and purveyor of fine musical flavours Mr. Pedro cooks up a banquet of aural delights every other week: afrobeat to disco and more, time to liven up.
The London based producer and DJ takes on the NTS airwaves…

Apiento, a.k.a Paul Byrne runs the invaluable Test Pressing blog and releases music on World Building, World Unknown and more. His show has that esoteric techno thing and whatever suits the mood…
From the host: "First show of the year and it's a nice mix of the old and the new. New music from Opal Sunn, Crooked Man, Tom Sharkett, Das Druid, Natural Magic, Apiento & Tepper, Make A Dance and Cherrie Bea. We start slow and go from there…"

LD and guests deliver a slice of realness via jazz, fusion, deep soul, funk, warm techno and the rest. Expect music you can move to from the long-time DJ and producer.
From the host: "Wanted to start the year nice and fast, but also jazzy, and inspired by Tim Reaper's recent Rare Groove mix on NTS, I've done a mix of Jungle and drum and bass that's influenced by jazz. Mostly stuff from around the mid-90s. Some absolute beautiful rolling tracks in there."

From 10 till midnight, Black Impulse’s shows are packed with transatlantic camaraderie and a distortion heavy stroll though metal, noise, gutter garage, trash blues, prog, hardcore, hip-hop, free jazz and anything else.

Adam digs deep into his box of 45s and pulls out a wild selection of 1950s and '60s blues, surf, rockabilly, R&B, gospel, garage, soul and rock'n'roll.
From the host: "Old mate Blind Benny joins me for a chat about his musical passions and DJ career."

nts2.d: A mixtape of Palestinian and Syrian wedding field recording in the north of the West Bank and south of Syria. By Ahmed Al Kilani, Mustafa Al Khatib, Abu Alil and many others.
Francesca Gavin talks to contemporary artists about their work, music, and the relationships between.

Steely Dan are beloved for being a rock band that is the antithesis of what a rock band should supposedly be. Forgoing the usual path of endless touring and explosive live performance, the core duo of Donald Fagen and Walter Becker focussed their energies in the studio. Over the years, they headhunted a rotating cast of  session musicians to execute their lofty and intricate musical projects, indebted to jazz as much as it was to the traditional rock canon. The music soundtracked Fagen's tales of modern malaise, laced with arch humour - a key facet of their now cult status.
Settle in for two hours of Steely Dan.

integration sounds from the source; an invitation into the shadow.

Shift into darker melly, early evenings and the tough emergence. Here's gustman again with some authumnal classics..

Irrevelent, asymmetric selections by Boomkat lifer, Conor Thomas; caretaker of The Death of Rave and R* T*** labels, and resident DJ of The White Hotel & Impiety Hour {AD England} in Manchester, drawing on decades of nocturbulous behaviour and a brend toward short-circuiting genres.
"bleep, bass, hardcore and jungle, dnb" this month - lock in.

Craig Clouse's genre-bending project Shit and Shine hijacks the NTS airwaves. Tune in on a Saturday for an hour of audio felonies spanning everything from post punk to dirty electro, techno or new wave.

Long time NTS collaborator and This City Plays producer, Brav brings a monthly showcase of ambient, techno and experimental cuts…
From the host: "classics and future classics"

Malibu is a French electronic musician whose work sails between ambient and ethereal music.
Forever inspired by soft reverbed vocals and melodious chord progressions, Malibu’s music is an immersive nostalgic journey in a sea of synthetic strings and choirs.

subtle.d: Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.

subtle.d: casual_observer is a DJ and producer originally hailing from Amsterdam, where he co-organises the "moving closer" event series with friend and collaborator Bcl-2. He currently resides in Berlin. Starting his musical journey as a drummer, his music retains a heavy focus on groove, rhythm and experimentation.  Sets played by casual_observer are diverse and surprising, moving effortlessly between jungle, breaks, bass, footwork, and more. No matter the genre, his selection is sure to keep you on your toes!

ixxi and Fei take you on a percussive journey with their show syncop8, moving from downtempo ambient to breaks, polyrhythms, and high energy beats, exploring every rhythmic and textural nuance in between.
Representing UK Bass Music Culture across a range of styles, sounds and tempos.

Rolling through varied tempo's and genres, Jimmy 2 Shoes brings dance floor orientated vibes and flows to wriggle your toes to. Expect eclectic selections and the freshest sounds from the UK underground.

As if kid is a professional Producer, DJ and Drummer from the west country (UK). Real name "Sid", He is versatile in producing hot records in various genres: Grime, UK Drill, Hip Hop, Jungle and more with an ever-growing number of global commercial placements and releases. He regularly collaborates with DJ Slimzee under alias E3 Breaks and with DJ Raggs under the alias Slamfire!

subtle.n: The Wheel Up Show w/ Tripta
subtle.d: Tripta is a Toronto based producer/DJ focusing on the darker sounds of Grime. Also blending elements of Drill, Dubstep and even Jungle all together for a unique sound you won't hear anywhere else. Signed to Slimzee's 'Slimzo's Recordings' and ‘Rotpot Records’.

Sound Arkitek is a Chicago hip-hop DJ with a love for all things drum & bass. 

With over 20 years experience playing house parties, raves, clubs and bars he has an encyclopedic knowledge of music but has always been a participant in jungle culture. In the early 2000s he was exposed to the genre primarily through Dieselboy and Danny The Wildchild mixes as well as the “Jungle Book” series of mixtapes. He became obsessed after hearing Bad Company’s “The Nine” and “Four Days,” as well as Pendulum’s “Vault.” 

As time went on, he got deeper into the scene, going to raves while buying records and posting on Drum & Bass Arena and DNBForum before turning 21 at which point he began going to Lava Lounge for Bass By The Pound’s “Seminar” series. The first legal drum & bass party he attended was Chase & Status at the aforementioned Lava Lounge, and he will never forget the energy when the duo played DJ Hazard’s “Killers Don’t Die” and it got a rewind. His love for the scene led to him playing drum & bass parties, opening for artists like Original Sin, Gridlok, and LTJ Bukem among others. 

His Subtle Radio show is an hour of the finest tunes in the scene at the moment. 

To keep up, follow @djsoundarkitek on Instagram!
With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

Jedah started DJ'ing at the tender age of 18 years of age specialising in UK Garage/Grime. 

Jedah is currently the DJ for Grime Original Hollowman Jendor of the former Grime Collective Essentials/ OG's.

Responsible for “that massive grime tune with the Psycho strings”, UK producers/DJs Trends & Boylan are well versed in what the scene has to offer. They use this platform to showcase music from across the 140 spectrum from Grime to Dubstep. Anything goes!!
